Howard Smith/USA Today SportsWhile Roy Hibbert's offensive game leaves much to be desired, he remains an elite shot-blocker. Back by popular demand, here's my second annual look at one-tool players, NBA specialists who can fill up a single category in fantasy basketball. All-round talents like LeBron James, Chris Paul and Russell Westbrook will be off the board quickly in fantasy drafts, so picking some of the names below might be more efficient ways to satisfy specific category needs. Here's a look at one-tool specialists who provide rebounds, 3-point shooting, blocks or steals. Rebounds Asik Omer Asik | New Orleans Pelicans 2013-14 rebounding: 7.9 per game (14.1 per 36 minutes) After a season spent being Dwight Howard's reluctant understudy, Asik is again free to reclaim his position as one of the best defensive centers in the game, playing the role of enforcer for Anthony Davis in New Orleans. Asik's brilliance on the defensive end relies heavily on positioning and contesting, and while it does not yield superlative numbers in the shot-blocking category, he is a dominant rebounder on both ends of the court. To read Amin Elhassan's full list of NBA specialists who can provide elite single-category production, sign up for Insider today. Insider Become an insider and get access to all our articles and tools. Subscribe Sign in View Insider Benefits Â» Magazine subscribers: activate your Insider account. Recommend0 Tweet0 Email Subscribe Amin Elhassan Follow Archive Video coordinator, college scout, Phoenix Suns Assistant director of basketball operations, Phoenix Suns MBA from Arizona State University